        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou2-sqa",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "SQA acceptance criteria — MRL 5 CFD solver",
        "description": "The CFD solver must be under formal version control, regression-tested against a suite of at least 20 canonical benchmark cases, and all identified defects triaged and resolved prior to production runs. Gradation 4 requires documented test coverage reports and formal change-control procedures."
      },
      "rationale": "The OpenFOAM-based solver branch used for this study is maintained under Git version control with tagged release v2.4.1-fda. A regression suite of 24 benchmark cases (lid-driven cavity, backward-facing step, rotating channel, Stokes flow) is executed on every merge to main; all 24 pass. A formal defect log is maintained; zero open critical defects at time of production runs. Change-control procedure documented in SQA-Plan-FDA-v3.2. Gradation 4 is achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-ncv",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou2-ncv",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Code verification acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Observed order of accuracy for velocity and pressure must be within 10% of theoretical order on at least 3 systematically refined meshes using the Method of Manufactured Solutions (MMS). Gradation 4 requires MMS verification for all governing equations including turbulence transport."
      },
      "rationale": "MMS verification was performed on the full Navier-Stokes plus k-omega SST system. Observed spatial order of accuracy: velocity 1.94 (theoretical 2.0, within 3%), pressure 1.91, turbulent kinetic energy 1.88. Three mesh levels (coarse/medium/fine) used. Results documented in Verification Report VR-FDA-2023-11. Gradation 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-de",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou2-de",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for the hemolysis index QoI must be below 5% on the production mesh. Richardson extrapolation must be performed on at least 3 mesh levels with refinement ratio >= 1.3. Gradation 4 requires GCI < 5% and documented asymptotic range confirmation."
      },
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (3.2M, 8.7M, 22.1M cells) with refinement ratio 1.36 were used. GCI for hemolysis index on production mesh (8.7M): 3.8%. Asymptotic convergence ratio 0.97 confirms solution in asymptotic range. Richardson-extrapolated hemolysis index used as baseline for validation comparison. Gradation 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-tc",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou2-tc",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet velocity profile, fluid viscosity, pump rotational speed) must be reproduced in simulation within stated measurement uncertainty. Gradation 4 requires documented traceability of all boundary condition values to calibrated measurement records."
      },
      "rationale": "All five operating points (3000/6000 RPM × 2.5/5.0/7.5 LPM) were reproduced using boundary conditions derived directly from the FDA bench protocol. Inlet velocity profiles measured by LDV; rotational speed verified by tachometer traceable to NIST. Fluid viscosity (glycerol-water, 0.00356 Pa·s) confirmed by calibrated rheometer. Full traceability matrix in Test Conditions Report TC-FDA-2023. Gradation 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-oc",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou2-oc",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Predicted hemolysis index must agree with bench measurements within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty bands across all 5 operating points. Gradation 5 additionally requires that the comparison metric (E_norm) be below 0.10 and that the comparison be performed using a formally documented validation metric."
      },
      "rationale": "Normalized validation metric E_norm computed per ASME V&V 20 for all 5 operating points. Values: 0.041, 0.067, 0.058, 0.072, 0.049 — all below 0.10 threshold. Experimental uncertainty bands (±8% hemolysis index) derived from inter-laboratory repeatability study. Simulation uncertainty from Monte Carlo propagation. All 5 points agree within combined uncertainty. Gradation 5 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-rqoi",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou2-rqoi",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The validation QoI (hemolysis index, velocity field) must be directly linked to the COU decision quantity (absolute hemolysis below clinical threshold). Gradation 4 requires a documented argument tracing validation QoIs to clinical risk endpoints."
      },
      "rationale": "The primary COU QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) in mg/dL. Validation experiments measure NIH directly using the same modified power-law hemolysis model applied in CFD post-processing. A QoI relevance matrix (QRM-FDA-2023) documents the causal chain from CFD shear stress → power-law damage accumulation → NIH → clinical hemolysis threshold (0.01 mg/dL). Gradation 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-rvac",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou2-rvac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Validation activity relevance acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, fluid, and operating regime as the COU. Gradation 4 requires documented similarity analysis covering geometry, Reynolds number, and hemolysis model applicability."
      },
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry (identical CAD to CFD model). Fluid: glycerol-water matching COU blood-analog viscosity. Operating points span the clinical VAD operating range (3000–6000 RPM, 2.5–7.5 LPM). Similarity analysis in Validation Relevance Report VRR-FDA-2023 confirms Re similarity within 4% across all points. Gradation 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-nse",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou2-nse",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical solver error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated by residual reduction of at least 5 orders of magnitude for all transport equations. Gradation 4 additionally requires that QoI monitor quantities show variation below 0.1% over the final 500 iterations."
      },
      "rationale": "All production runs achieved residual reduction of 6 orders of magnitude (continuity, momentum, k, omega). Hemolysis index monitor showed variation of 0.04% over final 500 iterations across all 5 operating points. Double-precision arithmetic used throughout. Iterative convergence report IC-FDA-2023 documents per-run convergence histories. Gradation 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-ue",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou2-ue",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Use error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "A documented simulation protocol must be followed by all analysts, with independent review of setup files prior to production runs. Gradation 3 requires a written simulation execution checklist and evidence of independent review sign-off."
      },
      "rationale": "Simulation Execution Checklist SEC-FDA-v2 was completed for each of the 5 operating point runs. An independent CFD engineer reviewed all mesh, boundary condition, and solver settings files before job submission; sign-off records retained in project document management system. No use errors identified in post-run audit. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-mf",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou2-mf",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The turbulence closure and hemolysis damage model must be justified by literature evidence for rotating blood-contacting flows. Gradation 4 requires a documented model form uncertainty analysis comparing at least two turbulence models and sensitivity of hemolysis index to model form choice."
      },
      "rationale": "k-omega SST and k-epsilon RNG closures were both run at all 5 operating points. Hemolysis index sensitivity to turbulence model choice: maximum 6.2% relative difference, within validation uncertainty band. Modified power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al., re-calibrated by Heuser & Opitz) selected based on published accuracy for rotary blood pump flows. Model form uncertainty documented in MFU-FDA-2023. Gradation 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-mi",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou2-mi",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria",
        "description": "All uncertain model input parameters must be characterized with probability distributions derived from measurement data or literature. Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation must be performed with at least 500 samples. Gradation 4 requires documented sensitivity indices (Sobol) identifying dominant input uncertainties."
      },
      "rationale": "Twelve uncertain inputs identified (fluid viscosity, pump clearance gaps ×4, inlet velocity profile shape, hemolysis model coefficients ×3, surface roughness ×3). PDFs assigned from measurement data and published ranges. Monte Carlo propagation: 1024 Latin Hypercube samples. First-order Sobol indices computed; dominant inputs are hemolysis model exponent (S1=0.41) and impeller tip clearance (S1=0.28). Results in Uncertainty Quantification Report UQR-FDA-2024. Gradation 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-ts",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou2-ts",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test samples acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Experimental data must be drawn from at least 3 independent test runs per operating point to support statistical characterization of measurement variability. Gradation 3 requires documented inter-run repeatability analysis."
      },
      "rationale": "FDA hemolysis bench dataset includes 3 independent test runs per operating point (15 runs total across 5 points). Inter-run coefficient of variation for NIH: mean 4.2%, max 7.8%. Repeatability analysis documented in Experimental Data Report EDR-FDA-2016-rev2. Sample sizes sufficient to characterize measurement uncertainty at Gradation 3. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-eip",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "The 'Equivalency of input parameters' factor in ASME V&V 40 addresses scenarios where computational model inputs are derived by mapping from a source domain (e.g., a predicate device or a scaled test article) to the COU domain, requiring demonstration that the mapped inputs are equivalent in their effect on the QoI. In this assessment, no such cross-domain input mapping is performed: the CFD model inputs are set directly from measurements taken on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry operated under the same fluid and rotational conditions as the COU. There is no predicate device substitution, no geometric scaling, and no parametric transfer from a surrogate test article. All boundary conditions are measured directly on the COU-representative hardware. Because the factor presupposes an input equivalency argument that is structurally absent from this assessment's evidence chain, applying the factor would require manufacturing a spurious equivalency claim where none exists. The factor is therefore not applicable to this package. This determination was reviewed and confirmed by the credibility assessment team lead on 2026-04-19."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-nc6-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team lead",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 12 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels at Model Risk Level 5. Software quality assurance (G4/G4), numerical code verification (G4/G4), discretization error (G4/G4), test conditions (G4/G4), output comparison (G5/G4), relevance of QoIs (G4/G4), relevance of validation activities (G4/G4), numerical solver error (G4/G4), use error (G3/G3), model form (G4/G4), model inputs (G4/G4), and test samples (G3/G3) all satisfy acceptance criteria. The 13th factor, Equivalency of input parameters, is not applicable because no cross-domain input mapping is performed in this assessment; all inputs are measured directly on the COU-representative hardware. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification (1024 LHS samples) confirms that hemolysis index predictions remain below the clinical threshold of 0.01 mg/dL across the full uncertain input space. Sobol sensitivity analysis identifies the hemolysis model exponent and impeller tip clearance as dominant uncertainty contributors, and targeted experimental characterization of both has been completed. The provenance chain is complete: all validation results are traceable to calibrated experimental datasets, and all simulation activities are documented with version-controlled solver inputs. The structured evidence base supports acceptance of the claim that the CFD model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for the Class III VAD device with sufficient credibility for regulatory submission.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
